FBIS4-67992 "jptot018__l94038" JPRS-TOT-94-018-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 26 April 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA INDIA Update on Investigation Into 1993 Bombay Bombs Update on Investigation Into 1993 Bombay Bombs BK2704020494 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 1630 GMT 26 Apr 94 BK2704020494 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network English BFN [Text] The Central Bureau of Investigation [CBI] has found evidence that arms training was imparted in a neighboring country to some of the accused in last year's Bombay blasts. A CBI spokesman said that two people have been arrested in this connection. The Bureau is said to have gathered more material against the prime accused in this case. It is alleged that the two arrested were sent abroad for training in handling explosives by another accused who is absconding. The CBI is reported to have made the breakthrough while checking the records of the regional passport office.
